---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../../components/Layout.astro";
import ImageHero from "../../components/ImageHero.astro";
import MissionBanner from "../../components/MissionBanner.astro";
import SectionHeader from "../../components/SectionHeader.astro";
import heroImage from "../../assets/founders-story/image4.jpg";
import littleGirl from "../../assets/founders-story/image11.png";
import rodeoOnDoc from "../../assets/founders-story/image5.jpg";
import founderWithHorse from "../../assets/founders-story/image9.jpg";
import threeChimigos from "../../assets/founders-story/image8.jpg";
import originalLogo from "../../assets/founders-story/image7.png";
import founderAndMother from "../../assets/founders-story/image3.jpg";
import threePigs from "../../assets/founders-story/image10.jpg";
import founderWithPigs from "../../assets/founders-story/image2.jpg";
import phinneasAndDonkey from "../../assets/founders-story/image1.jpg";
import rescueLogo from "../../assets/founders-story/image6.png";
---

<Layout title="Founder's Story" currentPath="/about/founders-story">
  <ImageHero
    headline="Our Founder's Story"
    subtext="A dream years in the making — built on rescue, resilience, and the quiet healing only animals can offer."
    image={heroImage}
    primaryCta={{ label: "Book a Tour", href: "/tours" }}
    secondaryCta={{
      label: "Explore Side by Side",
      href: "/healing-experiences",
    }}
    size="tall"
  />

  <section
    class="bg-off-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24"
    aria-labelledby="it-started-with-love"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="it-started-with-love"
        overline="A Dream Years in the Making"
        heading="It Started with Love"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>Some dreams begin with a business plan.</p>
        <p>Robin's Nest began with animals.</p>
        <p>
          As a little girl, I was always trying to rescue something. At five
          years old, it was a baby sparrow I named Tweety. Soon after came Doc,
          my beloved Quarter Horse, who became far more than a horse — he was my
          safe place, my confidant, and one of my earliest teachers in trust,
          resilience, and unconditional love.
        </p>
        <p>
          Long before I understood trauma or healing, animals were quietly
          teaching me both.
        </p>
        <p>That truth stayed with me for life.</p>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-12">
        <Image
          src={littleGirl}
          alt="The founder as a young girl outdoors, sitting in the grass."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full max-w-md rounded-lg shadow-md"
          widths={[400, 640, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 28rem, 100vw"
        />
      </figure>

      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <figure>
          <Image
            src={rodeoOnDoc}
            alt="The founder as a young rider competing on her Quarter Horse, Doc, in a rodeo barrel race."
            class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
            widths={[400, 640, 800]}
            sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
          />
          <figcaption
            class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
          >
            Riding Doc in the arena.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <Image
            src={founderWithHorse}
            alt="The founder as a young adult, cheek-to-cheek with her chestnut horse on a sunny day."
            class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
            widths={[400, 640, 800]}
            sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
          />
          <figcaption
            class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
          >
            A safe place, a confidant, a teacher.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="bg-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24"
    aria-labelledby="three-chimigos"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="three-chimigos"
        overline="Where the dream took its first step"
        heading="The Three Chimigos"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>
          In 2010, what would eventually become Robin's Nest took its first real
          step with a trip to the San Diego Humane Society.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's where I met Lily — a tiny tan Chihuahua mix who practically
          leapt into my heart. The connection was instant.
        </p>
        <p>
          Later came Alberto, a little blonde boy with a heartbreaking story of
          abuse, and Julio, a tiny black Chihuahua with a limp and an outsized
          spirit.
        </p>
        <p>
          Together, they became our beloved <strong>Three Chimigos.</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          Like the iconic <em>Three Amigos</em>, they became heroes to our
          family, our friends, and even thousands of college students who came
          to know them while accompanying my mother, Dr. Sue ("Nana"), in her
          teaching work.
        </p>
        <p>But they were more than adored companions.</p>
        <p>
          They became symbols of resilience, unconditional love, loyalty, and
          the extraordinary generosity animals offer — even after hardship.
        </p>
        <blockquote
          class="border-primary text-text my-6 border-l-4 pl-6 text-xl italic"
        >
          The soul of Robin's Nest owes much to these three little dogs.
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-12">
        <Image
          src={threeChimigos}
          alt="Three small rescue dogs — Lily the tan Chihuahua, Alberto the blonde, and Julio the black Chihuahua — standing together on a wooden deck."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
          widths={[400, 640, 1024]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 48rem, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption
          class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
        >
          Lily, Alberto, and Julio — the Three Chimigos.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="bg-off-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24"
    aria-labelledby="naming-the-dream"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="naming-the-dream"
        overline="2014"
        heading="Naming the Dream"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>
          By 2014, the dream had taken enough shape that I gave it a name:
          <strong>Robin's Nest.</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          Because my middle name is Robin, the name felt deeply personal — but
          it also represented everything I hoped to create:
        </p>
        <ul
          class="font-body text-text mx-auto max-w-md list-none space-y-1 pl-0 text-center text-lg"
        >
          <li>A place of shelter.</li>
          <li>Safety.</li>
          <li>Belonging.</li>
          <li>Home.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Even though the ranch didn't yet exist, the dream did.</p>
        <p>
          I believed in it enough to put it out into the universe —
          commissioning a graphic designer to create the very first Robin's Nest
          logo and giving life to a vision I hoped to build someday.
        </p>
        <p>But life has a way of making someday feel far away.</p>
        <p>
          Law school. Marriage. Starting my own business. A growing career.
          Responsibilities. Timing.
        </p>
        <p>And for years, the dream waited.</p>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-12">
        <Image
          src={originalLogo}
          alt="The original Robin's Nest Ranch Rescue Resort logo, featuring a horse silhouette on a teal and coral background."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full max-w-sm"
          widths={[300, 480, 640]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 24rem, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption
          class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
        >
          The very first Robin's Nest logo, commissioned in 2014.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24" aria-labelledby="leap-of-faith">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="leap-of-faith"
        overline="2020 and beyond"
        heading="The Leap of Faith"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>Then came the pandemic.</p>
        <p>
          Like so many people, the stillness of quarantine created space for
          reflection that everyday life rarely allows.
        </p>
        <p>I found myself asking difficult questions:</p>
        <p class="italic">
          What really matters?<br />
          What kind of legacy do I want to leave?<br />
          Why had I become so disconnected from the things that made me feel most
          alive?
        </p>
        <p>
          The answer kept bringing me back to the same place: animals, nature,
          healing, connection, and purpose.
        </p>
        <p>And the truth became impossible to ignore:</p>
        <blockquote
          class="border-primary text-text my-6 border-l-4 pl-6 text-xl italic"
        >
          Life is short. There is never going to be a perfect time.
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          If I was ever going to stop dreaming and actually build Robin's Nest,
          it had to be now.
        </p>
        <p>
          My mother, Dr. Sue, and I had long shared a deep love of animals and a
          belief in resilience, healing, and second chances. Together, we
          decided to take the leap.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="my-12">
        <Image
          src={founderAndMother}
          alt="The founder and her mother, Dr. Sue, smiling together — co-founders of Robin's Nest Rescue."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full max-w-md rounded-lg shadow-md"
          widths={[400, 640, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 28rem, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption
          class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
        >
          The founder with her mother and co-founder, Dr. Sue.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>
          When we found our five-acre property in Ramona — a former pig rescue —
          it wasn't polished.
        </p>
        <p>But it was full of possibility.</p>
        <p>
          We saw sanctuary. Second chances. A place where vulnerable animals
          could feel safe.
        </p>
        <p>
          And maybe, though we didn't fully realize it yet, a place where people
          could heal too.
        </p>
        <p>And then came our first sanctuary residents.</p>
        <p>
          Three little pigs — <strong>Falkor, Michael, and Meg</strong> — rescued
          from a legendary hoarding case through Farm Animal Refuge.
        </p>
        <p>
          I had originally gone to bring home the bonded pair, Falkor and
          Michael.
        </p>
        <p>But then Meg captured my heart.</p>
        <p>So naturally… I came home with three.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="my-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <figure>
          <Image
            src={threePigs}
            alt="Falkor, Michael, and Meg — three small black rescue pigs — looking up at the camera on a stone patio."
            class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
            widths={[400, 640, 800]}
            sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
          />
          <figcaption
            class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
          >
            Falkor, Michael, and Meg.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <Image
            src={founderWithPigs}
            alt="The founder sitting beside her three rescue pigs as they rest in the sun."
            class="h-auto w-full rounded-lg shadow-md"
            widths={[400, 640, 800]}
            sizes="(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw"
          />
          <figcaption
            class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
          >
            First sanctuary residents, first quiet afternoons.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>
          Soon after came <strong>Phinneas</strong>, a miniature horse, and
          <strong>Donkey</strong>, a miniature donkey, both saved from kill pens
          through Little Hooves.
        </p>
        <p>Suddenly, the dream wasn't just an idea anymore.</p>
        <p>It had names. Snouts. Hooves. Personalities. Stories.</p>
        <p>Robin's Nest was real.</p>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-12">
        <Image
          src={phinneasAndDonkey}
          alt="The founder leading Phinneas the miniature horse and Donkey the miniature donkey into a small barn at the sanctuary."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full max-w-2xl rounded-lg shadow-md"
          widths={[400, 640, 1024]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 42rem, 100vw"
        />
        <figcaption
          class="font-body text-text-light mt-2 text-center text-sm italic"
        >
          Phinneas and Donkey — saved from kill pens through Little Hooves.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="bg-off-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24"
    aria-labelledby="built-by-family"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="built-by-family"
        overline="The village"
        heading="Built by Family, Fueled by Community"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>Dreams like this don't happen alone.</p>
        <p>
          My mother, Dr. Sue, has been my co-founder, partner, and an
          extraordinary force behind Robin's Nest from day one.
        </p>
        <p>
          My husband, Nick, has also been one of Robin's Nest's greatest
          champions — supporting the vision, the uncertainty, and the leap of
          faith required to bring it to life.
        </p>
        <p>And then came the village.</p>
        <ul
          class="font-body text-text mx-auto max-w-md list-none space-y-1 pl-0 text-center text-lg"
        >
          <li>Friends.</li>
          <li>Volunteers.</li>
          <li>Neighbors.</li>
          <li>Donors.</li>
          <li>Community partners.</li>
          <li>Animal lovers.</li>
        </ul>
        <blockquote
          class="border-primary text-text my-6 border-l-4 pl-6 text-xl italic"
        >
          Robin's Nest has always been built by love.
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24" aria-labelledby="mission-grew">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="mission-grew"
        overline="An unexpected discovery"
        heading="When the Mission Grew"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>At first, Robin's Nest was about rescue.</p>
        <p>Saving animals. Creating sanctuary. Offering second chances.</p>
        <p>But something unexpected happened.</p>
        <p>When people came to the ranch, they changed.</p>
        <p>
          Guarded children opened up.<br />
          Stressed adults softened.<br />
          Stories surfaced.<br />
          Laughter returned.<br />
          Connection happened.
        </p>
        <p>
          Again and again, I witnessed the same quiet magic animals had given me
          my entire life.
        </p>
        <p class="font-heading text-primary text-center text-3xl">Healing.</p>
        <p>Not because of a formal program.</p>
        <p>
          Simply because animals have an extraordinary ability to meet us
          exactly where we are.
        </p>
        <p>
          And once I saw that happening — not just for me, but for others — I
          knew I couldn't keep it to myself.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    class="bg-off-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24"
    aria-labelledby="side-by-side"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="side-by-side"
        overline="A program born organically"
        heading="Side by Side"
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>
          That's how <strong>Side by Side</strong> was born.
        </p>
        <p>
          Not from a strategic plan — but organically, through community,
          connection, and lived experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          One visit became another.<br />
          One conversation became an invitation.<br />
          One invitation became a partnership.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today, Robin's Nest creates space for justice-impacted youth,
          veterans, first responders, trauma survivors, exonerees, and others
          navigating difficult chapters to experience the healing power of
          animals, nature, and connection.
        </p>
        <p>Because the mission became bigger than rescue.</p>
        <blockquote
          class="border-primary text-text my-6 border-l-4 pl-6 text-xl italic"
        >
          Healing goes both ways.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-center">
          <a
            href="/healing-experiences"
            class="text-primary font-semibold underline hover:no-underline"
          >
            Learn more about Side by Side
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-6 py-16 md:py-24" aria-labelledby="they-save-us">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <SectionHeader
        id="they-save-us"
        overline="Where the story keeps going"
        heading="We Rescue Them. They Save Us."
      />
      <div
        class="font-body text-text space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed [&_strong]:font-semibold"
      >
        <p>Robin's Nest Rescue is more than an animal sanctuary.</p>
        <p>
          It is a place where second chances are real.<br />
          Where healing happens quietly.<br />
          Where animals and humans alike are seen for more than their scars.
        </p>
        <p>Every animal here has a story.</p>
        <p>So do the people who walk through our gates.</p>
        <p>And somehow, side by side, healing happens.</p>
        <p>That is Robin's Nest.</p>
        <p>And we're just getting started.</p>
        <p
          class="font-heading text-primary mt-8 text-center text-3xl md:text-4xl"
        >
          We rescue them. They save us.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="mt-12">
        <Image
          src={rescueLogo}
          alt="The Robin's Nest Rescue mark with the tagline 'We rescue them. They save us.' arching above and below a horse, alpaca, and dog silhouette."
          class="mx-auto h-auto w-full max-w-sm"
          widths={[300, 480, 640]}
          sizes="(min-width: 768px) 24rem, 100vw"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <MissionBanner
    heading="Come meet the animals behind the story"
    body="The best way to experience Robin's Nest is in person. Book a Farm Tour to meet the animals, hear their stories, and see the sanctuary that grew from this dream."
    cta={{ label: "Book a Farm Tour", href: "/tours" }}
    variant="highlight"
  />
</Layout>
